<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="761" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12003.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The representatives of General
                            Huerta delegated to represent him at the conference called through the
                            mediation of Brazil, Argentina and Chile asked me, on their leaving
                            to-day for New York and Niagara Falls, to present in their names to your
                            excellency their earnest thanks for all the attentions and courtesies
                            extended to them since their arrival on American territory by your
                            excellency and the Department of State, which attentions and courtesies
                            they have appreciated to their full value.</p>
                        <p>In discharging this very pleasant duty, I avail [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>